'''David Møller Wolfe''' (born 23 April 2002) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] or [[left wing-back]] for {{English football updater|WolverhW}} club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]].

==Club career==
===Bergen and Brann===
Wolfe started his career in [[Bergen Nord FK|Bergen Nord]], playing on the senior team in 2017, 2018 and 2019 before joining the junior team of [[SK Brann]] in the summer of 2019. The same year, he became a Norway youth international player. In 2020, Wolfe was loaned out to [[Åsane Fotball|Åsane]] for the entire season.<ref name=nff>{{NFF|3210856}}</ref> In 2021 he signed a three-year contract with Brann.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.brann.no/nyheter/to-nye-unggutter-har-skrevet-langtidskontrakter|title=To nye unggutter har skrevet langtidskontrakter|date=1 February 2021|publisher=SK Brann|language=Norwegian|accessdate=9 May 2021}}</ref> He made his [[Eliteserien]] debut in May 2021 against Viking, as a left [[winger (football)|winger]].<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/players/david-moller-wolfe/603294/ Soccerway]</ref>

===AZ===
On 22 May 2023, Wolfe signed a five-year contract with Dutch [[Eredivisie]] club [[AZ Alkmaar]].<ref>{{Cite press release|url=https://www.az.nl/nl/nieuws/moller-wolfe-eerste-aanwinst-seizoen-2023-2024|title=Møller Wolfe eerste aanwinst seizoen 2023-2024|language=nl|publisher=[[AZ Alkmaar]]|date=22 May 2023|access-date=29 May 2023|archive-date=7 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230607221122/https://www.az.nl/nl/nieuws/moller-wolfe-eerste-aanwinst-seizoen-2023-2024|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
On 2 August 2025, Wolfe signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] on a five-year deal worth €10 million plus €2.1 million in add-ons.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20250802-wolves-bring-in-the-wolfe/|title=Wolves bring in the Wolfe|publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|date=2 August 2025|access-date=2 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Wolfe made his debut for the [[Norway national under-21 football team|Norway under-21 national team]] on 28 March 2023 in a match against [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal]]. He came on as a substitute, but Norway were defeated 3–0.

On 21 May 2026, Wolfe was included in the 26-man squad selected by [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]] manager [[Ståle Solbakken]] for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=1 June 2026 |date=21 May 2026 |language=en |title=Norway squad announcement |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/norway-squad-announcement-stale-solbakken |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

